gitmeta.rs:56), [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:60). A borrowed `contains` check before insertion keeps the common repeat-capture path cheaper.\\n\\nNo high-signal visibility, naming, or dependency-footprint issues jumped out; the public surface is small and the direct deps are source-used. I did not modify files. Validation was blocked because `Cargo.lock` currently contains unresolved conflict markers around [Cargo.lock](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/Cargo.lock:881), so `cargo test -p but-agentlog` cannot parse the lockfile.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T18:06:45.089Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"**Findings**\\n- [P1] Repeated captures still mutate GitMeta. `write_capture` always calls `write_session_metadata` even when no records are new, and that writes a fresh `updated-at` timestamp every run: [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:67), [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:137). If recapture is meant to be idempotent, gate this on actual appended/new records or make the “last seen” semantics explicit.\\n\\n- [P2] CWD validation requires every logged cwd to still exist. `validate_cwds` canonicalizes transcript cwd values before checking containment: [capture.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs:71). A valid session from a deleted nested directory under the repo will now fail as “cwd does not match,” which is surprising for historical logs.\\n\\n- [P2] GitMeta failures lose useful operation/key context. `write_capture` propagates raw errors from target parsing, session open, reads, set-adds, and list pushes: [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs